OL,3,CNetwork Rail warns people are 'risking
OL,4,Cit all' at level crossings
OL,6,FThomas Desmond, Network Rail
OL,7,FOperations Director, said: "Level
OL,8,Fcrossings demand your full attention,
OL,9,Fyet complacency and distraction are
OL,10,Fputting lives at risk, contributing to
OL,11,Fhundreds of dangerous near misses
OL,12,Fannually. Whether it's glancing at a
OL,13,Fphone or simply assuming the track is
OL,14,Fclear, these lapses in concentration
OL,15,Fcan be fatal. We urge everyone to
OL,16,Fstop, look, listen and obey the
OL,17,Fsignals every single time. Waiting a
OL,18,Ffew minutes is infinitely better than
OL,19,Frisking everything."
